PREAMBLE

The Glera-General-Public-Creative-License (GGPCL) is a free, copyleft license 
for software and other kinds of works, designed to ensure your freedom to share 
and change all versions of a program while prohibiting commercial exploitation, 
illegal activities, and military/harmful applications.

When we speak of free software, we are referring to freedom to use and modify, 
not price. Our Licenses are designed to make sure that you have the freedom to 
distribute copies of free software (and charge for them if you wish, as long as 
it's non-commercial), that you receive source code or can get it if you want it, 
that you can change the software or use pieces of it in new free programs, and 
that you know you can do these things - but NEVER for commercial gain, illegal 
purposes, or harmful applications.

To protect your rights, we need to prevent others from denying you these rights 
or asking you to surrender the rights. Therefore, you have certain responsibilities 
if you distribute copies of the software, or if you modify it: responsibilities 
to respect the freedom of others and to maintain the non-commercial, peaceful, 
and legal nature of the software.

For example, if you distribute copies of such a program, whether gratis or not, 
you must pass on to the recipients the same freedoms that you received. You must 
make sure that they, too, receive or can get the source code. You must ensure 
that they understand that the software is for non-commercial use only, must not 
be used for illegal activities, and must not be used for military or harmful 
purposes. And you must show them these terms so they know their rights and 
restrictions.

Developers that use the GGPCL protect your rights with two steps: (1) assert 
copyright on the software, and (2) offer you this License giving you legal 
permission to copy, distribute and/or modify it, subject to the terms herein.

