This prohibition applies regardless of how the commercial activity is structured, 
including but not limited to: direct sales, subscription services, freemium models, 
advertising-supported services, or any other revenue-generating mechanism.

You may charge a fee for the physical act of transferring a copy (such as media 
costs), but you may not charge for the software itself.

